{
  "texts": [
    "Molecular self-attentionIn this section, we give a short background on the prior works on adapting self-attention for molecular data and point out their potential shortcomings.Text Transformers.",
    "Multiple works have applied the Transformer directly to molecules encoded as text using the SMILES representation [14,15,29,30,38].",
    "SMILES is a linear encoding of a molecule into a string of characters according to a deterministic ordering algorithm [39,40].",
    "For example, the SMILES encoding of carbon dioxide is C(=O)=O.Adding a single atom can completely change the ordering of atoms in the SMILES encoding.",
    "Hence, the relative positions of individual characters are not easily related to their proximity in the graph or space."
  ]
}